            <note type="Gloss">
               <p xml:lang="en" source="#biblk000024-2"><term type="literal_translation">literally: stolen heart or stolen center construction (Kroll 458, 507, 585)</term> successive transverse projection (Guo 2002, 80); a <term ref="/keyword/k000172">huagong</term> which supports another timber extending perpendicular to the building plane (e.g. <term ref="/keyword/k000172">huagong</term>, <term ref="/keyword/k000103">ang</term>) without a crossing timber parallel to the building plane (e.g. guazigong, <term ref="/keyword/k000156">linggong</term>) (Fu 2017, 368; Chen 2010, 299).</p>
               <p xml:lang="zh-Hant" source="#biblk000024-3">鋪作出跳上交互斗口內，只承上一跳，不用橫栱的做法（陳 2010, 299)。</p>   
            </note>
